title: MSL/RAD Level 1 observational counter data - D. Hassler (SwRI-Boulder)

info.x_cadence_note: Cadence based on variable 'EPOCH' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/msl/rad/cdf/obs-l1/2015/msl_rad_obs-l1_2015002_v00.cdf. This most common cadence occurred for 48.8095% of the 41 timesteps. Cadence = 1021000000000 [ns] = PT1021S.

parameters.name: LET_A1_f
parameters.description: [Quality filtered] LET in A1 silicon detector. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function apply_filter_flag (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['LET_A1', 'FLAGGED_DATA']. Note that not all COMPONENTS are time series and so their values are not available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.

parameters.name: LET_A1
parameters.description: [All quality] LET in A1 silicon detector

parameters.name: LET_A2_f
parameters.description: [Quality filtered] LET in A2 silicon detector. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function apply_filter_flag (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['LET_A2', 'FLAGGED_DATA']. Note that not all COMPONENTS are time series and so their values are not available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
